The paper discusses coded caching schemes, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The focus on centralized and decentralized schemes suggests a possible fit with distributed computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the optimization of caching schemes could also be relevant to computer science and game theory (cs.CC).
